But anyway! It's fine. I set up the campaign so that it's really a series of smaller, mini adventures, and the next one is going to be a dwarf adventure! Dwarf mountain dungeon crawl adventure! And if you're curious, was I influenced by Delicious in Dungeon: YES. A  Senshi-like NPC will appear 😈

I'll check that one out! Thanks!! We have some tool (don't remember what it's called) on our computer for making maps but it's really only useful for setting up encounters, IMO. The last maps I had to make I did it old school with graph paper and a pencil

Haha :) when I agreed to DM our game, I forced my partner to agree to be the "DM Of Rules" which means doing all the math and reminding me of all the rules and what I'm supposed to be doing when we play 😅 but maps are still my responsibility, unfortunately

Haha :) I love creating the locations, imagining everything about the place, but then having to make the map?? I already did the hard work of coming up with it and now you're telling me I have to write it down, come on lol 😂

As the DM, I wish I could write the story and NPC characters dialogue, and create the settings, and write little paragraphs describing how spooky a place is, and then have someone else do literally everything else
It would be really helpful for my D&D campaign if I enjoyed creating maps. But, alas 😔

I still ask people to test if we're going to be meeting indoors, & I always offer to provide a test in case cost or access is an issue, and most people seem willing to, at least, humor us.
